{"TopicDetails": {"type": 0, "ccm2Id": 43134520, "cftId": 0, "identifier": "ISFP-2020-AG-FIRE", "title": "firearms trafficking", "publicationDateLong": 1599696000000, "callIdentifier": "ISFP-2020-AG-FIRE", "callTitle": "Call for proposals on the operational cooperation in the fight against firearms trafficking", "callccm2Id": 43134534, "allowPartnerSearch": true, "workProgrammepart": {"id": 280550, "ccm_id": 43061086, "wp_part": "ISFP-2020", "wp_year": "ISFP-2020", "wp_title": "Internal Security Fund Police", "wp_website": "http://ec.europa.eu/dgs/home-affairs/financing/fundings/security-and-safeguarding-liberties/internal-security-fund-police/index_en.htm", "wp_document": "https://ec.europa.eu/home-affairs/sites/homeaffairs/files/financing/fundings/security-and-safeguarding-liberties/internal-security-fund-police/union-actions/revised_annual_work_programme_isf_police_2020.pdf"}, "frameworkProgramme": {"id": 31077817, "abbreviation": "ISFP", "description": "Internal Security Fund Police"}, "programmeDivision": [{"id": 31077818, "abbreviation": "ISFP-2", "description": "Organised crime and human trafficking"}, {"id": 31078809, "abbreviation": "ISFP-2-7", "description": "Firearms"}, {"id": 31077824, "abbreviation": "ISFP-2-6", "description": "Law enforcement"}], "topicMGAs": [], "tags": ["gun crime", "law enforcement", "firearms trafficking"], "sme": false, "actions": [{"status": {"id": 31094503, "abbreviation": "Closed", "description": "Closed"}, "types": [{"typeOfAction": "ISFP-AG ISF-Police Action Grant", "typeOfMGA": []}], "plannedOpeningDate": "10 September 2020", "submissionProcedure": {"id": 31094504, "abbreviation": "single-stage", "description": "single-stage"}, "deadlineDates": ["10 December 2020"]}], "latestInfos": [], "budgetOverviewJSONItem": {"budgetTopicActionMap": {"3341997": [{"action": "ISFP-2020-AG-FIRE - ISFP-AG ISF-Police Action Grant", "plannedOpeningDate": "10 September 2020", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["10 December 2020"], "budgetYearMap": {"2020": 3000000}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}]}, "budgetYearsColumns": ["2020"]}, "description": "<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Scope</SPAN>:<p><span><span>Improved information sharing, research, data collection and analysis on the various aspects of firearms trafficking and gun crime are essential to compile a good intelligence picture and to keep up-to-date with evolving security needs. There is a need to improve the use of existing tools and assess possible synergies and interoperability between existing EU and international law enforcement databases to monitor the trafficking of firearms, inter alia by collecting, analysing and sharing relevant information. The call will support activities in the area of the fight against trafficking in firearms, aiming to facilitate joint initiatives and operational actions of EU countries associated with third partners; improve expertise in the area of firearms trafficking, in particular by enhancing knowledge, detection, investigation and prosecution at EU level and with key third countries; promote best practices inter alia concerning the defragmentation of the relevant information and intelligence along the firearms trafficking routes to and from the EU; safeguard the EU licit market as well as reduce diversion of firearms into criminal hands in the EU. </span></span></p>\n", "conditions": "<p><b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;&#xA;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#xA;color:#003366;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:&#xA;AR-SA\">1.&nbsp;&nbsp; Eligible countries: </span></b></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;&#xA;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#xA;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:&#xA;AR-SA\">All EU Member States, with the exception of Denmark, as well as the following third countries: Ukraine, Serbia, Montenegro, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Albania, Kosovo, North Macedonia, Tunisia, Lebanon, Jordan, Algeria, Morocco, Egypt and Switzerland.<br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>International organisations can be established outside the above-mentioned countries.</p>\r\n<p>United Kingdom is not bound by Regulation (EU) No. 513/2014  establishing the ISF Police instrument and its implementing decisions  and UK entities are therefore not eligible to participate under this  call.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;&#xA;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#xA;color:#003366;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:&#xA;AR-SA\">2.&nbsp;&nbsp; Eligibility and admissibility conditions:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;&#xA;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;&#xA;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"> </span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;&#xA;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;&#xA;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">see section 5 of the <a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/data/ref/other_eu_prog/home/wp/call-fiche_isfp-2020-ag-fire_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">call document</a><i>.</i></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;&#xA;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#xA;color:#003366;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:&#xA;AR-SA\">3.&nbsp;&nbsp; Indicative timetable for evaluation and grant agreement:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;&#xA;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;&#xA;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"> </span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;&#xA;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;&#xA;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;&#xA;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;&#xA;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">see section 3 of the <a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/data/ref/other_eu_prog/home/wp/call-fiche_isfp-2020-ag-fire_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">call document</a></span>.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#003366;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">4.&nbsp;&nbsp; Proposal templates and model grant agreements (MGA):</span></b></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#003366;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#003366;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#003366;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/data/ref/other_eu_prog/common/justdrugs-isfp-isfb-amif_guide-applicants-20_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Guide for applicants</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#003366;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#003366;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#003366;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial,Verdana,sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;\"> </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 102); font-family: &amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sans-serif&amp;quot;; font-size: 9pt; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/data/ref/other_eu_prog/common/tpl/pt/justdrugs-isfp-isfb-amif_call-pt-20_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Standard proposal template</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#003366;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#003366;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#003366;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\"><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/data/ref/other_eu_prog/common/justdrugs-isfp-isfb-amif_mga-multi_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">M</a></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\"><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/data/ref/other_eu_prog/common/justdrugs-isfp-isfb-amif_mga-multi_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">ulti-beneficiary Model Grant Agreement</a></span></span></span></p>\n<p>Members of consortium are required to conclude a consortium agreement, in principle prior to the signature of the grant agreement.</p>\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;&#xA;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#xA;color:#003366;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:&#xA;AR-SA\">5.&nbsp;&nbsp; Additional documents:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;&#xA;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#xA;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:&#xA;AR-SA\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;&#xA;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#xA;color:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-bidi-language:&#xA;AR-SA\"><br />\r\n</span> </span></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/data/ref/other_eu_prog/home/wp/call-fiche_isfp-2020-ag-fire_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Call document</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/home-affairs/sites/homeaffairs/files/financing/fundings/security-and-safeguarding-liberties/internal-security-fund-police/union-actions/docs/awp_isfp_2020_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">ISF-P Annual Work Programme 2020</span></span></a></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">ISF-P legal basis</span></span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">: <a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/data/ref/other_eu_prog/home/legal/isfp-legalbasis_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Regulation (EU) No 513/2014</a> and <a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/data/ref/other_eu_prog/home/legal/isfp-legalbasis2_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Regulation (EU) No 514/2014</a></span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&#xA;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\"><a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:32018R1046&amp;rid=9\" target=\"_blank\">EU Financial Regulation</a></span></span></p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>", "supportInfo": "<p>Contact the&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:HOME-ISF@ec.europa.eu\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>HOME-ISF@ec.europa.eu</strong></a> for further assistance related to content of the call and topics.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/portal/screen/support/faq;categories=;programme=null;actions=;keyword=\" target=\"_blank\">F&amp;T Portal FAQ</a></strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Submission of proposals.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/portal/screen/support/helpdesks/contact-form\" target=\"_blank\">IT Helpdesk</a></strong>&nbsp;&ndash; contact the IT helpdesk for questions such as forgotten passwords, access rights and roles, technical aspects of submission of proposals, etc.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/portal4/desktop/en/funding/guide.html\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>H2020 Online Manual</strong></a> -<strong> Please use the manual with caution and only for the Participant Portal tools guidance</strong>, i.e. Submission service and Beneficiary register. It is H2020 specific and does not cover the ISFP rules. Some aspects of these funds are different from the provisions of the H2020 programme.</p>", "sepTemplate": "<p>To access the Electronic Submission Service, please click on the submission-button next to the type of action that corresponds to your proposal. You will then be asked to confirm your choice of the type of action and topic, as these cannot be changed in the submission system. Upon confirmation, you will be linked to the correct entry point.</p>\r\n<p>To access existing draft proposals for this topic, please login to the Funding &amp; Tenders Portal and select the My Proposals page of the My Area section.</p>", "links": [], "additionalDossiers": [], "infoPackDossiers": [], "callDetailsJSONItem": {"staticAdditionalInfo": "<p><span><span>Improved information sharing, research, data collection and analysis on the various aspects of firearms trafficking and gun crime are essential to compile a good intelligence picture and to keep up-to-date with evolving security needs. There is a need to improve the use of existing tools and assess possible synergies and interoperability between existing EU and international law enforcement databases to monitor the trafficking of firearms, inter alia by collecting, analysing and sharing relevant information. The call will support activities in the area of the fight against trafficking in firearms, aiming to facilitate joint initiatives and operational actions of EU countries associated with third partners; improve expertise in the area of firearms trafficking, in particular by enhancing knowledge, detection, investigation and prosecution at EU level and with key third countries; promote best practices inter alia concerning the defragmentation of the relevant information and intelligence along the firearms trafficking routes to and from the EU; safeguard the EU licit market as well as reduce diversion of firearms into criminal hands in the EU. </span></span></p>\n", "latestInfos": [{"approvalDate": "Sep 10, 2020 1:27:31 PM", "lastChangeDate": "Sep 10, 2020 1:27:31 PM", "content": "The submission session is now available for: ISFP-2020-AG-FIRE(ISFP-AG)"}], "hasForthcomingTopics": false, "hasOpenTopics": false, "allClosedTopics": true}}}